- A graph that can be colored with 2 colors. Such that, no 2 adjacent nods have the same color.
- 2 colors can be anything like 0 or 1 || red or yellow || something 2 colors
- If a graph has even length cycle or Linear graph, then it is considered as Bipartite graph
- If a graph has odd length cycle, then it is not considered a bipartite graph.
- An input graph can be disconnected graph and it mean's that the graph may not be connected, meaning there may be two nodes
  u and v such that there is no path between them.
- A graph is bipartite if the nodes can be partitioned into two independent sets A and B such that every edge in the graph
  connects a node in set A and a node in set B. Return true if and only if it is bipartite graph. Otherwise, false.
